==English==

===Etymology===

From French ''reconnoître'' (obsolete spelling of ''reconnaître'').  Contrarily, there is also an obsolete 19th C UK English spelling ''reconnaitre'' (now ''reconnoitre'').

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˌrɛkəˈnɔɪtə/}} (''[[RP]]'')
*{{IPA|/ˌrɛkəˈnɔɪtɚ/}} (''US'')
*{{audio|en-us-reconnoiter.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Alternative spellings===
*(''mostly British'') [[reconnoitre]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

#To [[survey]] something (generally an [[enemy]]'s land and position).
#:''Our scout will '''reconnoiter''' the path ahead of our troops.''

====Synonyms====
* [[scout]], [[survey]]

